channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: White House Provides Unfortunate Money Quote for Kamala Harris As She Distances Herself From Joe Biden
Window to define Harris rapidly closing as favorability rating rises in new poll
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' approval rating is rising, surging past both President Biden and former President Trump in a new poll.

item.title: Speaker to Citizens: Read Report on Biden's Conduct
item.description: House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., urged Americans to read the GOP report on what the three-committee impeachment inquiry called President Joe Biden's "impeachable conduct."

item.title: Comrade Kamala DNC Special: 60% Off VIP Membership
Fetterman spokeswoman reamed for reportedly contradicting boss on Israel: 'Unparalleled hubris'
item.description: Carrie Adams, communications director for Sen. John Fetterman, reportedly told a reporter she disagrees with her boss' stance on Israel and claimed the younger generation shares a more nuanced view.

item.title: DA Bragg: No Opposition to Trump Sentencing Delay
item.description: Manhattan prosecutors in the Donald Trump business records trial said they would defer to the court when it comes to whether the former president's sentencing should be delayed.

item.title: Democrats Release Official Party Platform: It's Both Laughable and Obscene in Its Lies
Bipartisan lawmakers put UN on notice over 'rampant anti-Israel bias'
item.description: Reps. Mike Lawler and Jared Moskowitz are spearheading a bill threatening U.S. funding to the United Nations if it moves to restrict Israel's access to the international body.

item.title: Biden Will 'Finish the Job,' Chief of Staff Says
item.description: White House chief of staff Jeff Zients told Axios on Monday that President Joe Biden will "finish the job" and be productive during his final five months in office.

item.title: NEW: House Judiciary Report Shows Joe Biden Committed Multiple Impeachable Offenses
SEE IT: Protests erupt, businesses board up outside the DNC in Chicago
item.description: Images show protesters gathering outside of the Democratic National Convention (DNC), and police brace for unrest throughout the four-day event.

item.title: David Axelrod: Trump 'May Well' Win Electoral Vote
item.description: Longtime Democrat strategist David Axelrod warned party leaders that former President Donald Trump "may well" win the election if it were held now.

item.title: NEW: The Nasty Move Pelosi Reportedly Made to Push Biden Out
Former President Bill Clintonâ€™s second term as POTUS was entangled with scandal, ended with impeachment
item.description: Bill Clinton spent two terms in the White House from 1993 until 2001. Following his own presidential term, he supported his wife, Hillary, in her run for office in 2016.

item.title: Suffolk PBA President to Newsmax: Biden-Harris Leadership 'Abject Failure' for Police
item.description: The leadership coming out of the White House during President Joe Biden's term in office has done nothing to help the state of policing in America, Suffolk County Police Benevolent Association (PBA) President Lou Civello told Newsmax on Monday.
